.TH HIDLOOM-HIDD 8 "@HIDLOOM_VERSION@" "HIDloom" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
hidloom-hidd \- native USB HID report broker
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hidloom-hidd
[\fB--frames\fR \fIN\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hidloom-hidd
receives canonical HID report frames from a local socket and writes keyboard,
mouse, consumer, and US-sub keyboard reports to the configured USB gadget
endpoints.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --frames N
Process a bounded number of frames, mainly for tests.
.TP
.B -h, --help
Show command help.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
\fBUSBD_HID_REPORT_SOCKET\fR, \fBUSBD_HID_REPORT_PATH\fR,
\fBUSBD_US_SUB_HID_REPORT_PATH\fR, and timing variables control broker paths
and retry behavior.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR hidloom-outputd (8),
.BR usbd (8)
.br
